<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Calron</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-27 15:42:59</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This spell is up there with one of the best Druid spells in the game and one of the most underutilized by young Druids.  For picking a part camps this is great!  you can harmony the MOBs then snare the MOB you want and pull him alone out of the camp. </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: AutoBond</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-28 12:40:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I recommend you use this spell on any camp you want to hunt at no matter what. In any camp cast it on the lowest mob so it has the best chance for success. If any other mob is nearby it will effect them as well. I use this on all camps just to make sure there is no some sneaky mog hiding in a tent, or around a pillar that I did not see before.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
